<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1926,2024]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="385" pageId="0" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1926,1952]" pageId="0" pageNumber="384">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Raimundi &amp; Domínguez &amp; Salles, 2021" authorityName="Raimundi &amp; Domínguez &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2021" box="[283,635,1926,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boldrinii" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis box="[283,391,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="384">Miroculis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[410,518,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="384">Miroculis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[537,635,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="384">boldrinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[645,737,1926,1952]" pageId="0" pageNumber="384">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[645,737,1926,1952]" pageId="0" pageNumber="384" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Edmunds" authorityYear="1963" box="[1128,1236,1926,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1128,1236,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="384">Miroculis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters. Male imago: 1) head orange strongly tinged with dark brown; 2) dorsal portion of compound eye on a short stalk, with the inner margin presenting a medial projection (
<figureCitation box="[1085,1151,1998,2024]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="384">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) and dorsal surface with 20 facets on the longest row; 3) fore wing hyaline except for three wide dark brown transversal bands; 4) forceps segment II 0.24× forceps segment I; 5) forceps segment I with subdistomedial protuberance; and 6) forceps brown with inner margin paler on segments II and III.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
