<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1456,2023]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,1149]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="387" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,430,1456,1482]" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">MEASURES (mm)</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[448,506,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Body</emphasis>
: 6.0. Fore wing: 4.7; angularity of cubital region 94°; hind wing: 1.4. Fore and middle legs: broken off and missing; hind leg: 3.5. Penis: 0.8. Caudal filament: broken off and missing. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1324,1429,1492,1518]" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">RATIOS</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,219,1529,1554]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Wings</emphasis>
: Fore wing width 0.5× fore wing length; hind wing length 0.3× fore wing length; hind wing width 0.6 hind wing length; fork on MA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[433,441,1583,1597]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">2</subScript>
of fore wing 0.5× total length of MA. 
<emphasis box="[875,928,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Legs</emphasis>
: segments of hind leg: 0.92: 1.00 (
<quantity box="[1319,1425,1565,1591]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.41" pageId="2" pageNumber="386" unit="mm" value="1.41">1.41 mm</quantity>
): 0.07: 0.06: 0.06: 0.08. 
<emphasis box="[401,507,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Genitalia</emphasis>
: medial length of styliger plate 0.6× maximum width of styliger plate; lateral length of styliger plate 0.7× medial length of styliger plate; lateral length of styliger plate 1.1× lateral length of segment IX. Forceps segment III 0.7× segment II; segment III 0.3× segment I; segment II 0.4× segment I; penis length 1.5× forceps segment I. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[363,555,1708,1734]" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">COLORATION</emphasis>
: General coloration: orangish brown. 
<emphasis box="[981,1042,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Head</emphasis>
: Orangish and strongly tinged with dark brown. Stalk of compound eye black; upper portion with facets separated by dark grooves. Ocellus white surrounded by gray. Antenna brownish. 
<emphasis box="[573,654,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Thorax</emphasis>
. Sclerites yellowish brown. Pleura pale; pleural sclerites tinged with dark gray. Ventral surface of cervix with a posteromedial dark gray spot. Pro, meso and metanotum tinged with brown, margins of sclerites darker. 
<emphasis box="[553,621,1853,1878]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[638,743,1852,1879]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Figs 2–3</figureCitation>
): Fore wing hyaline marked with two evident wide brownish transversal bands (
<figureCitation box="[359,428,1888,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Hind wing hyaline, brownish on apical 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[889,908,1891,1917]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">⅕</emphasis>
and around cross veins (
<figureCitation box="[1184,1252,1888,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1273,1326,1889,1914]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Legs</emphasis>
. Hind leg whitish. Coxa and femur tinged with light brown; femur with dark brown complete band on median and subapical portions. 
<emphasis box="[257,363,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Orangish brown, translucent and tinged with light brown. Tergum IX with posterior gray mark; terga I–VIII with postero-sublateral grayish brown triangular mark; grayish brown marks on posterolateral area of tergum I–VII, and on antero-sublateral areas of terga VI–VII. Sternites orangish brown, translucent; darker on I–VI; sternite X with lateral orangish marks. Spiracles brownish; tracheae gray. 
<emphasis box="[964,1070,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1083,1185,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Figs 4–5</figureCitation>
): Styliger plate brown. Forceps brown, inner margin of forceps segment II and III lighter (
<figureCitation box="[885,952,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Penis dark brown medially, lighter toward base and apex. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[319,531,258,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">MORPHOLOGY</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[544,605,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Head</emphasis>
: posterior margin V-shaped. Upper portion of compound eye on short stalk (wider than long), separated medially by distance of one compound eye; medial projection of dorsal surface present (
<figureCitation box="[160,227,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface elongated with 20 facets on longest row. 
<emphasis box="[894,975,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Thorax</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[991,1059,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1077,1181,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Figs 2–3</figureCitation>
). Three bullae visible; 14 cross veins between C and Sc, 10 distal to bulla; fork of MA strongly asymmetric; fork of MP slightly (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1423,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Hind wing with apex acute; costal projection poorly developed; Sc ends distally of apex of costal projection; fork of R+MA slightly asymmetric; MP free basaly; CuP present; Anal vein absent (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1103,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1124,1230,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1244,1347,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Figs 4–5</figureCitation>
): lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[221,289,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); styliger plate with posteromedial portion concave. Forceps segment I with basal third broad, tapering gradually toward apex, and inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1111,510,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
, arrow). Base of penis broad tapering abruptly toward apex; base of inner margin with row of spines (
<figureCitation box="[963,1031,546,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,283,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-64@1.[157,1429,270,1913]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Miroculis (Miroculis) boldrinii sp. nov., male imago: 1) Scheme of the dorsum of the head indicating medial eye projection (arrow); 2) Fore wing; 3) Hind wing; 4) Genitalia (lateral view); 5) Genitalia (ventral view): arrow shows the inner margin with subdistomedial portion broader of forceps." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4701031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4701031/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
