<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="387" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1149]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,870,896]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Raimundi &amp; Domínguez &amp; Salles, 2021" authorityName="Raimundi &amp; Domínguez &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2021" box="[339,607,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boldrinii" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis box="[339,447,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Miroculis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[463,494,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[509,607,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">boldrinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[614,703,871,897]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[614,703,871,897]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
shares some characteristics with 
<taxonomicName authority="Savage, 1987" authorityName="Savage" authorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosus" subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis box="[1076,1184,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Miroculis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1200,1308,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Miroculis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">nebulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Savage, H. M." box="[151,303,907,933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" pagination="97 - 108" refId="ref4967" refString="Savage, H. M. (1987) Two new species of Miroculis from Cerro de la Neblina, Venezuela with new distribution records for Miroculis fittkaui and Microphlebia surinamensis (Ephemeroptera: Leptophlebiidae). Aquatic Insects, 9, 97 - 108. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01650428709361279" type="journal article" year="1987">Savage, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
such as a medial projection on the inner margin of the compound eye, basal half of penis broad and tapering abruptly toward the apex, and base of the styliger plate broader than apex. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Raimundi &amp; Domínguez &amp; Salles, 2021" authorityName="Raimundi &amp; Domínguez &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2021" box="[1240,1436,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boldrinii" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis box="[1240,1271,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1289,1320,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1338,1436,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">boldrinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,241,979,1005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,241,979,1005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Savage" authorityYear="1987" box="[390,595,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosus" subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis box="[390,421,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[437,467,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[483,595,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">nebulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having 20 facets on the longest row of upper portion of compound eye, instead of 
<quantity box="[269,367,1015,1041]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.175" metricValueMax="3.556" metricValueMin="2.794" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" unit="in" value="12.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="11.0">11–14 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Savage" authorityYear="1987" box="[375,581,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosus" subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis box="[375,405,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[422,453,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[469,581,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">nebulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the presence of dense pigmentation on the membrane of fore wings and by the size of penis, shorter than the combination of the styliger plate and forceps in the new species. Fore wings of both species are also distinct; in 
<taxonomicName authority="Raimundi &amp; Domínguez &amp; Salles, 2021" authorityName="Raimundi &amp; Domínguez &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2021" box="[546,737,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boldrinii" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis box="[546,569,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[593,624,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[639,737,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">boldrinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[744,834,1087,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[744,834,1087,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
three wide and complete brown transversal bands are present, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Savage" authorityYear="1987" box="[344,549,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Miroculis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosus" subGenus="Miroculis">
<emphasis box="[344,367,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[391,414,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[437,549,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">nebulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
these bands are narrower and incomplete.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
